WEBVTT

00:02.394 --> 00:03.744
<i> Previously on</i> Monarch...

00:03.896 --> 00:05.395
-I love you.
-I love you more.

00:05.414 --> 00:07.006
Just because he's gone back
to London for a while,

00:07.233 --> 00:08.749
-it doesn't mean that he...
-We know exactly
what it means, Mom.

00:08.901 --> 00:11.068
We're in this family, too, and
some things you just can't hide.

00:11.161 --> 00:12.368
KAREN:
And the winner is...

00:12.370 --> 00:14.329
Nicky Roman for "God Knows."

00:14.406 --> 00:16.240
-(cheering, applause)
<i> -NICKY: I can't focus</i>

00:16.333 --> 00:19.076
<i> on what I've won, I can only</i>
<i> think about what I've lost.</i>

00:19.094 --> 00:21.353
-You and Gigi will work it out.
-Then there's us.

00:21.580 --> 00:23.263
Some things are worth
waiting for.

00:23.357 --> 00:26.174
TRIPP:
That's the woman you had
an affair with, right?

00:26.268 --> 00:28.585
<i> -ALBIE: Yeah.</i>
<i>-TRIPP: Rosa died in that fire,</i>

00:28.604 --> 00:31.196
<i> but she gave birth</i>
<i> to a little girl.</i>

00:31.348 --> 00:34.366
-Mine?
-According to her
birth certificate...

00:35.852 --> 00:36.869
<i> ...yes, sir.</i>

00:36.978 --> 00:38.779
I promise, Mama,

00:38.931 --> 00:40.597
<i> I won't let them forget you.</i>

00:40.616 --> 00:42.857
You should go see Nicky
to make things right.

00:42.877 --> 00:44.768
I half agree with you.

00:44.861 --> 00:47.454
I'm gonna go over there
and tear that bitch a new one.

00:47.531 --> 00:49.531
Maybe it's time I had a word
with Nicky Roman.

00:49.608 --> 00:53.177
Set that woman straight
once and for all.

00:55.297 --> 00:57.723
♪ ♪

01:16.652 --> 01:18.327
(banging on door)

01:28.981 --> 01:31.406
Clive, what're you doing here?

01:31.500 --> 01:33.908
I was just doing a bit
of thinking about us.

01:33.928 --> 01:34.927
You're drunk.

01:35.245 --> 01:37.096
(laughs) That's when I do
my best thinking.

01:37.247 --> 01:38.597
Do you mind if I, uh...?

01:39.658 --> 01:43.435
You're supposed to be
on a plane tonight, Clive.

01:43.587 --> 01:46.012
Well, I was, but then I thought,
you know, why leave?

01:46.165 --> 01:47.272
This is where my home is.

01:47.499 --> 01:49.942
-My family and my wife.
-Mm-hmm.

01:50.169 --> 01:52.277
Well, you broke those things
a long time ago,

01:52.504 --> 01:53.612
including me.

01:53.763 --> 01:55.021
Nicky,

01:55.174 --> 01:57.507
you are the love of my life.

01:57.526 --> 01:59.860
Yes, until you started sleeping
with your co-stars.

01:59.954 --> 02:01.845
Ah, mistakes, all of them.

02:01.864 --> 02:03.180
Come on, come on, Nicky.

02:03.273 --> 02:04.289
Please, come on, don't do this.

02:04.516 --> 02:06.416
Do what? Tell my wife
how much I love her?

02:07.703 --> 02:09.110
I'm sorry, I really am.

02:09.130 --> 02:11.797
Wow. How sorry are you?

02:11.948 --> 02:14.040
Excuse me?

02:14.135 --> 02:15.525
Hmm?

02:15.544 --> 02:18.545
No. Clive, I really don't think
this is a good idea.

02:18.714 --> 02:21.198
-Maybe I don't care
what you think.
-(screams)

02:21.216 --> 02:23.142
I mean, you and your family,

02:23.327 --> 02:24.977
you think the rest of the world
are like chess pieces,

02:25.128 --> 02:27.204
to be moved around
as you see fit. Expendable.

02:27.297 --> 02:29.314
-Don't you? Hmm?
-Clive!

02:29.541 --> 02:32.876
Well, guess what, Nicky?
Hmm? I'm not.

02:32.895 --> 02:35.687
What if you're
expendable, eh? Hey?

02:35.839 --> 02:38.640
Do you think the world
would even miss you, hmm?

02:38.659 --> 02:40.975
-Would they even notice? Huh?
-Please...

02:40.995 --> 02:41.976
Would they even care?

02:41.996 --> 02:44.997
Answer me!
(grunts)

02:48.669 --> 02:50.669
(gasping)

02:56.735 --> 02:59.736
Oh, my God, Gigi.

02:59.905 --> 03:01.972
<i> (phone ringing)</i>

03:04.243 --> 03:06.185
-Hey, kiddo.
-Daddy.

03:06.412 --> 03:08.245
<i> Something really</i>
<i> terrible has happened.</i>

03:08.263 --> 03:10.022
I don't know what to do.

03:10.173 --> 03:11.839
Don't move. I'll be right there.

03:11.859 --> 03:15.110
(whimpers, panting)

03:31.027 --> 03:33.528
No cops?

03:33.622 --> 03:36.289
Last thing this family needs
is more scandal.

03:36.366 --> 03:38.866
-He tried to kill Nicky.
-ALBIE: I know,

03:38.961 --> 03:41.127
but you bring cops
and lawyers in,

03:41.204 --> 03:42.870
and the truth can get

03:42.965 --> 03:45.115
awful complicated.

03:45.133 --> 03:48.042
Now, go clean yourselves up,

03:48.062 --> 03:50.044
get ahold of your brother.

03:50.064 --> 03:52.105
I'll take care of this.

03:56.904 --> 03:58.445
(engine starts)

04:12.828 --> 04:14.211
(sighs)

04:22.263 --> 04:23.553
♪ ♪

04:34.474 --> 04:36.024
Oh, hell nah.

04:42.432 --> 04:43.782
(yells)

04:43.933 --> 04:45.742
(both grunting)

04:52.942 --> 04:54.543
(gunshots)

04:58.857 --> 05:00.874
(Clive panting)

05:00.968 --> 05:03.376
"Texas Truth-teller." (laughs)

05:03.529 --> 05:05.429
I've always wondered why
they called you that, Albie.

05:06.640 --> 05:08.807
'Cause as far as I can tell,

05:09.034 --> 05:11.393
all the Romans do is lie.

05:15.983 --> 05:19.059
And now, you're hiding.

05:19.211 --> 05:21.486
I always knew that
you were a liar, Albie.

05:21.638 --> 05:23.613
I just never thought
you were a coward!

05:29.145 --> 05:30.478
(door closes)

05:30.497 --> 05:32.739
(gunshots)

05:32.833 --> 05:34.499
(grunting)

05:35.952 --> 05:38.061
(groaning)

05:38.080 --> 05:40.464
A Roman never forgets a friend.

05:41.900 --> 05:44.092
Or an enemy.

05:50.576 --> 05:52.434
♪ ♪

05:57.524 --> 06:00.275
♪ ♪

06:06.200 --> 06:08.182
♪<i> Sometimes I don't know</i> ♪

06:08.276 --> 06:10.443
♪<i> Where this dirty road</i> ♪

06:10.596 --> 06:13.096
♪<i> Is taking me</i> ♪

06:13.189 --> 06:16.666
♪<i> Sometimes I don't even know</i>
<i> the reason why</i> ♪

06:18.194 --> 06:21.028
♪<i> But I guess</i>
<i> I'll keep gambling</i> ♪

06:21.048 --> 06:22.956
♪<i> Lots of booze and lots of</i> ♪

06:23.108 --> 06:24.791
♪<i> Rambling</i> ♪

06:24.943 --> 06:26.276
Rest in peace.

06:26.294 --> 06:29.779
♪<i> It's easier than just</i>
<i> waiting around</i> ♪

06:29.798 --> 06:32.282
♪<i> To die...</i> ♪

06:32.300 --> 06:35.285
Can I ask your father
a few questions?

06:35.454 --> 06:37.971
♪<i> Ah, one time, friends,</i>
<i> I had a ma</i> ♪

06:38.123 --> 06:40.399
♪<i> Even had a pa</i> ♪

06:41.885 --> 06:45.645
♪<i> He beat her with a belt once</i>
<i> 'cause she cried</i> ♪

06:45.797 --> 06:48.073
I'm saying we better get
to that body before they do.

06:48.224 --> 06:49.649
♪<i> I tried to kill the pain</i> ♪

06:49.743 --> 06:52.636
♪<i> Bought some wine</i>
<i> and hopped a train...</i> ♪

06:52.729 --> 06:54.579
Oh, hell.

06:54.731 --> 06:56.915
♪<i> Seemed easier</i> ♪

06:57.066 --> 07:00.293
♪<i> Than just waiting</i>
<i> around to die.</i> ♪

07:03.165 --> 07:06.040
Clive was the blackmailer,
wasn't he?

07:06.151 --> 07:09.319
Sure sounded like it.

07:09.412 --> 07:12.914
He could recite our sins,
chapter and verse.

07:12.933 --> 07:15.341
It's not over, is it?

07:15.494 --> 07:17.919
Listen, we've done what we can.

07:17.938 --> 07:20.188
<i> Took care of the evidence.</i>

07:21.608 --> 07:24.192
<i> Staged Clive's disappearance.</i>

07:25.094 --> 07:26.169
<i> Stashed his car.</i>

07:26.262 --> 07:29.339
What about the body?

07:29.357 --> 07:31.508
Trust me, I ain't forgetting,

07:31.601 --> 07:33.768
but there's nothing
to do right now,

07:33.862 --> 07:35.695
so...

07:35.847 --> 07:38.698
go inside, hug your babies.

07:38.792 --> 07:41.960
<i> Try to get some sleep.</i>

07:42.187 --> 07:43.962
<i>The rest is tomorrow's problem.</i>

07:53.882 --> 07:56.141
I saw it all.

07:56.292 --> 07:58.051
I don't care what you think.

07:58.203 --> 07:59.719
I saw Dad attack you.

07:59.796 --> 08:01.128
Answer me!

08:01.223 --> 08:02.731
I saw how Aunt Gigi stopped him.

08:05.877 --> 08:07.134
NICKY:
Daddy?

08:07.154 --> 08:09.321
We're in here, Nick.

08:12.826 --> 08:14.067
Where's the boy?

08:14.219 --> 08:17.537
He's okay.
He just wanted to be alone.

08:18.982 --> 08:20.240
He's such a good boy.

08:20.392 --> 08:21.891
Barely 18. How could I let him

08:21.910 --> 08:23.484
get involved in any of this?

08:23.578 --> 08:25.987
We're family, and we take care
of one another.

08:26.006 --> 08:27.230
He understands that.

08:27.249 --> 08:29.582
We are family, and...

08:29.735 --> 08:31.510
tonight, we went through
something that no family

08:31.737 --> 08:33.419
should ever have to. We've done
what needs to be done,

08:33.514 --> 08:36.998
and... we've taken care
of what needs

08:37.092 --> 08:38.258
to be taken care of.

08:38.352 --> 08:39.684
We have to stay close
on this one.

08:39.761 --> 08:41.269
All of us.

08:43.190 --> 08:45.006
GIGI:
Sorry, I was just clearing

08:45.025 --> 08:46.841
-my head.
-Hey, Geeg.

08:46.860 --> 08:48.610
We're putting in.

08:49.863 --> 08:51.738
Hi.

08:53.349 --> 08:55.200
Your mama always said
that the truth

08:55.277 --> 08:57.369
is what you say it is.

08:57.596 --> 08:59.112
So, like Nicky said,

08:59.264 --> 09:01.540
we got to stick together.

09:01.767 --> 09:04.117
Stick to our truth.

09:04.193 --> 09:05.377
As long as we stay together,

09:05.528 --> 09:06.878
we can move on.

09:07.030 --> 09:09.138
♪<i> Well, together</i> ♪

09:09.140 --> 09:12.575
♪<i> We're gonna</i>
<i> wait around to die</i> ♪

09:13.720 --> 09:16.780
♪<i> Yeah, together we're gonna</i>
<i> wait around</i> ♪

09:16.873 --> 09:21.059
♪<i> And die.</i> ♪

09:34.466 --> 09:37.150
<i> TRIPP:</i>
<i> So, you reported Clive missing</i>

09:37.302 --> 09:39.077
-about a month ago, right?
-Mm-hmm.

09:39.228 --> 09:41.471
It was after the CML Awards.

09:41.489 --> 09:43.640
Uncle Tripp, if it's, uh,
if it's bad news,

09:43.733 --> 09:44.824
you can just tell us.

09:44.918 --> 09:46.492
Not bad news, it's-it's no news.

09:46.645 --> 09:49.312
You know, usually, when folks
go missing, we get hits

09:49.405 --> 09:51.815
pretty quick from the Rangers,

09:51.908 --> 09:54.259
or ICE if they
cross the border, but...

09:55.987 --> 09:58.746
Nicky, is there
anything you haven't

09:58.765 --> 10:00.081
told us?

10:00.100 --> 10:03.435
Anything that could
help us find him?

10:03.586 --> 10:04.769
You already know that,

10:04.938 --> 10:07.180
after I ended the marriage
with Clive,

10:07.332 --> 10:08.848
he didn't take it very well.

10:09.000 --> 10:10.442
There, um...

10:10.669 --> 10:13.945
there was another woman
he was seeing in California.

10:14.097 --> 10:16.281
She wasn't the first

10:16.432 --> 10:17.841
or the only.

10:17.934 --> 10:19.100
I'm-I'm sorry, Nick.

10:19.119 --> 10:21.328
That's-that's the truth.

10:23.365 --> 10:26.273
Nicky, I know you're worried,

10:26.368 --> 10:27.851
but Clive's got a bit
of a bird dog

10:27.869 --> 10:31.129
in him, so dollars to donuts,
he's shacked up somewhere.

10:31.280 --> 10:33.022
Exactly what I said.

10:33.116 --> 10:34.615
TRIPP:
Okay, so

10:34.635 --> 10:35.692
y'all hear anything,

10:35.785 --> 10:37.469
call me, 24/7. Meanwhile,

10:37.696 --> 10:38.953
we're on it.

10:38.972 --> 10:41.839
But in my experience,

10:41.992 --> 10:45.551
sometimes husbands
don't want to be found.

10:45.704 --> 10:48.104
Yeah. Thanks.

10:49.465 --> 10:50.798
<i> NICKY:</i>
<i> I hate lying like that.</i>

10:50.817 --> 10:53.985
Oh, you played it perfect, Nick.
It was concern,

10:54.212 --> 10:56.488
not panic. Ugh...

10:56.639 --> 10:58.214
Those tears.

10:58.233 --> 11:00.307
Those tears were real
because I'm scared. Aren't you?

11:00.360 --> 11:03.887
All I know is right now,
the only thing we can control

11:03.905 --> 11:05.330
is what's right in front of us.

11:05.481 --> 11:08.908
As a Roman,
that means one thing.

11:09.060 --> 11:12.228
This family needs
to get back to normal.

11:12.247 --> 11:14.655
Normal? After what we did?

11:14.675 --> 11:15.915
What I did?

11:15.992 --> 11:17.658
Hang on now, Georgina,
your brother's right.

11:17.752 --> 11:20.494
That is a phrase I was certain
I'd never hear.

11:20.514 --> 11:22.906
Like it or not,
our lives are public.

11:22.999 --> 11:25.350
Which is why we're
going back to work.

11:25.501 --> 11:27.577
Starting with Gigi's
photo shoot for<i> Beaucoups</i>

11:27.579 --> 11:29.503
magazine this weekend.
You're welcome.

11:29.523 --> 11:31.106
And the rest of us...

11:33.084 --> 11:34.508
...we're getting in
the liquor game.

11:34.528 --> 11:35.935
Starting with
the Truthteller launch

11:36.029 --> 11:36.677
at the 'Wheel
this Thursday night.

11:36.697 --> 11:38.104
'Cause nothing says,

11:38.347 --> 11:40.440
"I put that murder behind me"
like finger food and free booze.

11:40.592 --> 11:41.925
It's all arranged.

11:41.943 --> 11:43.609
Press, influencers.

11:43.762 --> 11:45.929
We've even got Wade Stellings
who's gonna perform.

11:45.947 --> 11:48.264
Well, that won't be awkward.

11:48.283 --> 11:51.601
As long as Nicky
performs with him.

11:51.619 --> 11:53.861
I've told you, I haven't made
my mind up about singing yet.

11:53.880 --> 11:55.029
I think Gigi's right.

11:55.198 --> 11:56.940
I don't think this is
the time to do a launch.

11:57.033 --> 12:00.126
If we want it to look like
we got nothing to hide, it is.

12:00.295 --> 12:02.220
LUKE:
Truthteller.

12:02.371 --> 12:04.797
American whiskey. Named...

12:04.950 --> 12:06.799
after Albie Roman himself.

12:06.893 --> 12:09.102
How did you get
that nickname, Daddy?

12:10.138 --> 12:11.712
Came from your mama,

12:11.732 --> 12:13.714
long time ago.

12:13.734 --> 12:16.276
Story for another day.

12:19.889 --> 12:21.722
Catch up with y'all later.

12:21.891 --> 12:23.491
-See you, Daddy.
-Bye, Daddy.

12:25.579 --> 12:27.579
(sighs)

12:27.730 --> 12:29.472
("I'm a Wanted Man"
by Royal Deluxe playing)

12:29.565 --> 12:31.641
-♪<i> I'm a wanted man</i> ♪
-(shouts, grunting)

12:31.734 --> 12:33.476
♪<i> I got blood on my hands</i> ♪

12:33.495 --> 12:36.070
-Oh!
-♪<i> Do you understand...</i> ♪

12:36.089 --> 12:37.814
-(banging on door)
-MANAGER: Mr. Roman?

12:37.832 --> 12:39.983
This is hotel management.

12:40.001 --> 12:42.835
We've had some complaints
about the noise.

12:42.988 --> 12:44.654
(shouts)

12:44.714 --> 12:46.306
Is that any better?

12:47.993 --> 12:51.344
♪<i> I'm a wanted man.</i> ♪

12:51.496 --> 12:53.012
Call the police.

12:53.164 --> 12:54.680
Nobody's calling anybody.

12:54.833 --> 12:55.774
Mrs. Roman.

12:56.001 --> 12:58.334
Hello. I am so sorry.

12:58.427 --> 13:00.612
You know, my husband
had a very bad reaction

13:00.763 --> 13:02.688
to a prescription pill,

13:02.857 --> 13:04.357
and I-I-- we'll of course pay

13:04.509 --> 13:06.767
for all the damages,
and my family

13:06.861 --> 13:09.178
really appreciates
your understanding,

13:09.197 --> 13:11.864
and, of course, your discretion.

13:12.017 --> 13:14.350
And I'll take it from here.

13:14.369 --> 13:15.460
Thank you.

13:18.131 --> 13:20.781
Dottie Cantrell Roman.

13:20.801 --> 13:23.784
Queen of Country.
To what do I...

13:23.804 --> 13:25.744
Houston,

13:25.806 --> 13:27.697
Tacoma, Tuscaloosa.

13:27.790 --> 13:30.883
Must you humiliate yourself
in every corner of this country?

13:30.977 --> 13:33.127
I get lonely on the road.

13:33.146 --> 13:35.538
Bull. You're scared.

13:35.540 --> 13:38.708
Scared? Of what?

13:38.726 --> 13:40.318
The truth.

13:40.545 --> 13:43.062
You used to play arenas,
now you're playing clubs.

13:43.214 --> 13:45.490
You haven't written
a new song in years,

13:45.641 --> 13:49.052
and I am so sick of flying in
from God knows where

13:49.054 --> 13:50.720
to clean up all your mess

13:50.813 --> 13:52.664
because you're feeling
sorry for yourself.

13:52.815 --> 13:55.741
I can handle myself just fine.

13:55.894 --> 13:57.836
Well, do it then,

13:58.063 --> 14:01.422
because this Queen is done.

14:04.678 --> 14:06.427
Goodbye, Albie.

14:18.099 --> 14:19.265
Oh, my goodness,
you really shouldn't have gone

14:19.417 --> 14:20.507
to all this trouble, Earl.

14:20.527 --> 14:22.343
Please, I made this
for your mama every time

14:22.362 --> 14:24.195
she fired the cook. Eat up.

14:24.422 --> 14:26.105
Then we'll try on some new looks

14:26.199 --> 14:28.107
for the bourbon launch.

14:28.259 --> 14:29.942
Nothing gets
the creative juices flowing

14:30.095 --> 14:32.111
like handsome men
and hard liquor,

14:32.280 --> 14:33.687
or vice versa.

14:33.765 --> 14:36.190
Wait a second, you're really
performing at that thing?

14:36.209 --> 14:39.210
No, Tatum.
Earl is jumping the gun.

14:39.362 --> 14:41.754
I haven't made my mind up yet.

14:43.199 --> 14:44.883
More taters, anybody?

14:45.034 --> 14:47.594
Straight from the
Kenny Rogers cookbook.

14:49.723 --> 14:51.464
I'll have some more.

14:51.616 --> 14:53.449
Sure, go ahead.

14:53.468 --> 14:55.042
Act like everything is normal

14:55.136 --> 14:56.619
when I haven't heard
from Dad in a month.

14:56.712 --> 14:58.379
EARL:
Maybe I should

14:58.398 --> 15:01.399
power down the curling iron.

15:03.052 --> 15:05.978
Right, Tatum, I'm...
I'm sorry, honey.

15:06.131 --> 15:07.739
Look, I know this is
a very hard time.

15:07.890 --> 15:10.967
This family acts like
it's all about authenticity.

15:10.985 --> 15:12.652
But what's going on here

15:12.804 --> 15:15.538
is not normal, no matter
what you guys say.

15:21.829 --> 15:22.979
What about you?

15:22.997 --> 15:25.481
-How you doing?
-I'm okay, Mom.

15:25.500 --> 15:26.240
Really.

15:26.259 --> 15:28.426
But it's gonna be okay.

15:28.619 --> 15:30.094
All right?
We're gonna be strong.

15:30.321 --> 15:31.245
We're gonna get through this

15:31.264 --> 15:33.598
'cause we're Romans.

15:42.000 --> 15:44.517
♪ ♪

15:44.669 --> 15:46.502
Wow. What's all this for?

15:46.595 --> 15:48.446
All this is for you.

15:49.282 --> 15:52.158
And this is just the beginning.

15:54.788 --> 15:56.770
("Get Higher"
by Ma Baker playing)

15:56.790 --> 15:58.181
♪<i> Na, na, na, na, na, na, na</i> ♪

15:58.199 --> 15:59.749
♪<i> Get higher</i> ♪

16:00.627 --> 16:02.377
♪<i> Get higher</i> ♪

16:03.112 --> 16:04.353
♪<i> Get higher...</i> ♪

16:04.372 --> 16:06.189
One sec, hon.
Quick hair touch-up.

16:06.207 --> 16:08.007
♪<i> Get higher...</i> ♪

16:09.194 --> 16:12.211
How do you feel?
You look incredible.

16:12.363 --> 16:14.955
Actually, it's kind of fun.
Can't believe I'm gonna be

16:15.049 --> 16:17.383
on the cover
of<i> Beaucoups</i> magazine.

16:17.535 --> 16:19.477
Me and Nicky used to steal
Mama's copies all the time.

16:19.628 --> 16:20.627
-Look at me now.
-Yes!

16:20.647 --> 16:22.371
You should feel
so proud of yourself.

16:22.465 --> 16:23.539
Honestly?

16:23.632 --> 16:24.816
I do.

16:24.967 --> 16:26.300
(laughs)

16:26.319 --> 16:29.395
-(winces) I'm just...
Uh, my lipstick.
-Oh.

16:29.489 --> 16:32.115
-Just need to keep...
Yeah. Yeah.
-Oh, right.

16:43.911 --> 16:44.836
Mr. Roman.

16:45.063 --> 16:47.413
Albie.

16:47.565 --> 16:49.340
Uh, Catt and...

16:49.492 --> 16:51.050
you'd be Ana, is that right?

16:52.086 --> 16:54.012
We just had a meeting
with your son.

16:54.163 --> 16:55.662
He doesn't think Ana is ready

16:55.757 --> 16:57.498
for a solo album yet.

16:57.592 --> 16:59.258
Well, you hang in there.

16:59.410 --> 17:02.395
And remember,
never trust the suits.

17:03.857 --> 17:04.856
Okay.

17:05.083 --> 17:07.508
Nice to see you, Mr. Roman.

17:07.527 --> 17:09.218
Excuse me.

17:09.270 --> 17:12.012
That locket you're wearing,

17:12.032 --> 17:13.698
where'd that come from?

17:13.849 --> 17:15.733
It was my grandmother's.

17:15.960 --> 17:17.518
I never got to meet her, but

17:17.612 --> 17:20.279
she left it to my mom,
and my mom left it to me.

17:20.431 --> 17:22.356
CATT:
It's nice to have
an heirloom to pass on

17:22.450 --> 17:23.616
to my daughter.

17:23.935 --> 17:26.544
No matter how far she goes,
she will always remember

17:26.695 --> 17:29.121
where she came from.

17:29.274 --> 17:31.424
Take care, Mr. Roman.

17:36.056 --> 17:37.221
What is so important

17:37.298 --> 17:38.781
that you called me
all the way in here?

17:38.874 --> 17:40.707
If this is about Wade and the...

17:40.802 --> 17:43.043
the bourbon launch, I'm still
on the fence about that.

17:43.063 --> 17:46.122
Well, then you'd better get
your butt off that barbed wire

17:46.124 --> 17:48.974
because Mackenzie Gates
from Open Horizon is coming

17:49.051 --> 17:50.735
tomorrow, and if you
knock it out of the park,

17:50.962 --> 17:52.570
she's gonna put you in every

17:52.721 --> 17:53.979
major arena in North America.

17:54.132 --> 17:56.074
Why would you do this now?

17:56.225 --> 17:58.317
Why would I engineer you
a national tour

17:58.411 --> 18:00.060
and catapult your career
to the next level?

18:00.154 --> 18:02.729
After what we've done?

18:02.749 --> 18:05.065
And where Tatum's head's at? No.

18:05.159 --> 18:06.325
My head's not
in the right place.

18:06.419 --> 18:09.328
-I'm not doing it.
-Let me ask you a question.

18:09.480 --> 18:10.846
Do you think that
anybody out there

18:10.848 --> 18:12.739
gives a damn about your truth?

18:12.759 --> 18:15.593
This is a golden opportunity

18:15.820 --> 18:17.244
for you and this company.

18:17.263 --> 18:20.080
So, you are gonna summon up
your best Dottie Roman,

18:20.174 --> 18:22.416
and you're gonna
get on that stage,

18:22.510 --> 18:26.162
and you're do
what she did, pretend.

18:26.180 --> 18:28.180
Just like Gigi's
doing right now.

18:28.333 --> 18:31.067
Show must go on, Nick.

18:34.856 --> 18:36.489
Thank you.

18:38.118 --> 18:40.676
-Hey.
-Hey.

18:40.769 --> 18:43.103
What brings you here?

18:43.197 --> 18:44.455
I needed to grab
some audio files

18:44.607 --> 18:46.365
for the demos your dad
and I are working on.

18:46.517 --> 18:49.127
-Mm-hmm.
-He said the guitars sounded,

18:49.354 --> 18:51.462
uh... (chuckles) thin.

18:51.581 --> 18:53.189
(laughs) Yeah,

18:53.207 --> 18:56.025
-I bet he didn't use that word.
-No, he did not.

18:56.118 --> 18:57.209
You know, I was wondering why

18:57.362 --> 18:58.878
I haven't heard from you.
I texted you

18:59.030 --> 19:00.546
a couple of times
after the CMLs.

19:00.698 --> 19:04.049
Um, yeah, I'm sorry. Um,
I've just had a lot going on.

19:04.202 --> 19:07.145
I get it, really.
No hard feelings.

19:08.648 --> 19:10.039
Nicky, the-the award

19:10.132 --> 19:13.058
you got was just the beginning.

19:13.153 --> 19:14.986
People are finally starting to
see you for who you really are,

19:15.213 --> 19:16.879
not just your mother's daughter.

19:16.898 --> 19:19.282
Thank you.

19:20.218 --> 19:22.643
Anyway, I'd better get going.

19:22.662 --> 19:25.204
Good seeing you.

19:27.725 --> 19:29.375
<i> (guitar playing)</i>

19:30.728 --> 19:33.579
Mr. Roman? Your son just
sent this over for you.

19:33.731 --> 19:36.990
Oh, thank you, Cal.
Just set it down right here.

19:37.084 --> 19:38.509
Appreciate it.

19:54.919 --> 19:57.420
-(distant music playing)
-(crowd cheering)

19:57.513 --> 19:59.680
You sure you're up for
a sold-out stadium tonight?

19:59.699 --> 20:02.258
I'm good. I just lost 250 pounds

20:02.351 --> 20:03.592
of reckless, drunken cowboy,

20:03.611 --> 20:05.536
and I feel better
than I ever have.

20:05.688 --> 20:07.112
Before you say anything,

20:07.265 --> 20:09.690
this time, it is for good.

20:09.709 --> 20:10.766
Of course it is, gorgeous.

20:10.785 --> 20:12.268
Of course it is.

20:12.286 --> 20:14.045
(sighs)

20:16.532 --> 20:19.199
What the hell
are you doing here?

20:19.219 --> 20:21.552
I came here to serenade you

20:21.779 --> 20:23.779
in front of your fans.

20:23.798 --> 20:26.282
Just like
in Jacksonville in '82.

20:26.375 --> 20:27.558
And Macon in '84.

20:27.710 --> 20:29.618
You know, I was younger then
and more forgiving.

20:29.712 --> 20:31.729
-Get out.
-Baby...

20:31.880 --> 20:33.731
Oh, don't you "baby" me.
I told you

20:33.958 --> 20:36.976
the last time, it was the last
time, and I mean what I say,

20:37.128 --> 20:39.886
and I'm over
these stunts of yours.

20:39.906 --> 20:41.239
Using my fans to convince me

20:41.466 --> 20:42.965
-to take you back.
-ALBIE: You'll feel different

20:42.984 --> 20:44.316
when you hear me sing,

20:44.393 --> 20:48.487
and when you see how much
that crowd believes in us,

20:48.581 --> 20:49.655
you will again, too.

20:49.807 --> 20:51.123
No, Albie.

20:52.401 --> 20:54.326
Okay, babe, if you don't
want me going out there,

20:54.420 --> 20:55.736
you're gonna have to stop me.

20:55.830 --> 20:57.646
That can be arranged.

20:57.665 --> 20:59.423
Yeah.

21:00.167 --> 21:01.984
-(gunshot)
-(gasps)

21:02.077 --> 21:03.652
(grunting)

21:03.671 --> 21:06.079
Don't you scream.
We both know you had it coming.

21:06.099 --> 21:08.674
You shot me in the leg.

21:08.826 --> 21:11.660
Yeah, I guess I missed
my mark by a few inches.

21:11.679 --> 21:13.271
My shot always did veer
to the left.

21:13.422 --> 21:15.147
Excuse me.

21:16.183 --> 21:18.567
Try not to die
before I finish my set.

21:20.929 --> 21:22.855
(crowd cheering)

21:23.007 --> 21:24.615
(groans)

21:34.777 --> 21:37.036
♪<i> How lucky, how lucky</i> ♪

21:37.130 --> 21:39.705
♪<i> Can any</i> ♪

21:39.857 --> 21:43.408
♪<i> Girl be...</i> ♪

21:43.469 --> 21:44.451
Hello.

21:44.545 --> 21:47.138
I was surprised
to hear from you.

21:47.289 --> 21:50.474
I'm not so sure I believe that.

21:52.053 --> 21:53.978
You know who I am.

21:55.206 --> 21:58.374
That necklace your daughter
was wearing.

21:58.467 --> 22:00.484
I gave one just like it
to someone,

22:00.711 --> 22:02.728
long time ago.

22:02.880 --> 22:04.739
Someone I knew very well.

22:06.400 --> 22:07.808
You're lucky.

22:07.943 --> 22:09.902
I never knew her at all.

22:10.071 --> 22:13.497
But she was your mother, right?

22:16.894 --> 22:19.462
Which makes you my daughter.

22:23.509 --> 22:27.178
Your girl, Ana, does she
know anything about this?

22:28.997 --> 22:30.497
No.

22:30.516 --> 22:33.184
And I'd like it
to stay that way.

22:33.335 --> 22:34.167
So...

22:34.261 --> 22:37.429
what do you want from us?

22:37.582 --> 22:39.765
I just want Ana
to have the chance

22:39.859 --> 22:42.768
to show the world
how talented she is.

22:42.920 --> 22:44.603
That she's got
the same God-given gift

22:44.755 --> 22:47.031
her grandfather has.

22:47.258 --> 22:49.408
And that's all?

22:50.761 --> 22:53.037
You're wondering
if I want something for myself.

22:54.765 --> 22:57.357
I was raised with nothing.

22:57.377 --> 22:58.617
Nothing.

22:58.711 --> 23:01.528
And I'm good with that.

23:01.697 --> 23:04.340
But if you want to put
your guilt to good use...

23:06.293 --> 23:09.345
...just remember
your granddaughter.

23:18.472 --> 23:21.732
♪ ♪

23:26.480 --> 23:27.696
(tablet chimes)

23:30.985 --> 23:31.984
Yes.

23:32.303 --> 23:33.802
The mock-ups from
the photo shoot are here.

23:33.821 --> 23:35.061
Wow, that was fast.

23:35.081 --> 23:36.639
Kind of promised
the photographer another gig

23:36.732 --> 23:38.807
if he slipped it to us early.
Don't say anything.

23:38.859 --> 23:39.975
(both laugh)

23:39.994 --> 23:41.752
(gasps)

23:41.979 --> 23:46.006
Girl, you are mega-snatched.

23:47.318 --> 23:51.336
Oh, my Lord, this is
a game changer, baby.

23:51.431 --> 23:53.013
(sighs)

23:54.325 --> 23:55.507
You don't like them?

23:55.660 --> 23:59.252
For 20 years,
I've battled to live my truth.

23:59.272 --> 24:02.014
I fought my teachers, pastors,

24:02.166 --> 24:04.257
my own mother, for God's sakes.

24:04.426 --> 24:05.759
But...

24:05.778 --> 24:07.427
these are beautiful.

24:07.521 --> 24:09.354
Those pictures are a lie, Kayla.

24:09.507 --> 24:11.115
That doesn't look
anything like me.

24:11.342 --> 24:12.265
I don't want any part of that.

24:12.359 --> 24:14.026
Do you know how hard it was

24:14.178 --> 24:15.511
to get you this cover shoot?

24:15.529 --> 24:16.679
Well, I don't care.

24:16.697 --> 24:18.197
That big-haired, painted-up,

24:18.291 --> 24:20.106
airbrushed woman there...

24:20.201 --> 24:22.960
that ain't me.

24:25.965 --> 24:27.539
(sighs)

24:27.692 --> 24:29.550
<i> (door opens)</i>

24:31.195 --> 24:33.545
-(door closes)
-Oh, hey.

24:33.639 --> 24:35.047
Glad y'all could make it.

24:35.199 --> 24:37.290
Thank you for calling us.

24:37.310 --> 24:38.867
-Yeah.
-ANA: Thanks for asking me,

24:38.886 --> 24:40.144
Mr. Roman.

24:40.371 --> 24:41.645
Well, it's my pleasure.

24:43.316 --> 24:45.191
All right, let's go to work.

24:49.230 --> 24:50.821
All right, don't be nervous.

24:50.973 --> 24:53.324
Music's in your blood.
I can tell.

24:54.568 --> 24:56.660
(band playing
"Half of My Hometown")

25:08.415 --> 25:11.917
♪<i> Half of my high school</i>
<i> got too drunk</i> ♪

25:12.011 --> 25:15.161
♪<i> Half of my high school</i>
<i> fell in love</i> ♪

25:15.330 --> 25:18.849
♪<i> With the girl next door</i> ♪

25:19.076 --> 25:21.644
♪<i> In their daddy's Ford</i> ♪

25:23.022 --> 25:25.764
♪<i> Half of my Main Street's</i>
<i> miniskirts</i> ♪

25:25.916 --> 25:29.342
♪<i> Half of my Main Street's</i>
<i> dressed for church</i> ♪

25:29.436 --> 25:32.254
♪<i> It could use some rain</i> ♪

25:32.347 --> 25:35.181
♪<i> And a fresh coat of paint</i> ♪

25:35.201 --> 25:39.278
♪<i> Half of my hometown's</i>
<i> still hanging around</i> ♪

25:39.430 --> 25:42.540
♪<i> Still talking about</i>
<i> that one touchdown</i> ♪

25:42.767 --> 25:45.617
♪<i> They're still wearing</i>
<i> red and black</i> ♪

25:45.711 --> 25:47.878
♪<i> Go Bobcats</i> ♪

25:48.105 --> 25:50.697
♪<i> While the other half</i>
<i> of my hometown</i> ♪

25:50.791 --> 25:52.608
♪<i> They all got out</i> ♪

25:52.626 --> 25:56.111
♪<i> Some went north,</i>
<i> some went south</i> ♪

25:56.130 --> 25:59.131
♪<i> Still looking for a feeling</i> ♪

25:59.225 --> 26:02.726
♪<i> Half of us ain't found</i> ♪

26:02.878 --> 26:04.136
♪<i> So stay or leave</i> ♪

26:04.288 --> 26:06.138
♪<i> Part of me</i> ♪

26:06.290 --> 26:09.600
♪<i> Will always be</i> ♪

26:09.752 --> 26:12.069
♪<i> Half of my hometown</i> ♪

26:14.799 --> 26:18.576
♪<i> Back roads raise us</i> ♪

26:18.727 --> 26:21.061
♪<i> Highways, they take us</i> ♪

26:21.080 --> 26:23.972
♪<i> Memories make us</i> ♪

26:23.991 --> 26:27.492
♪<i> Want to go back</i> ♪

26:27.661 --> 26:29.494
♪<i> To our hometown</i> ♪

26:29.663 --> 26:31.755
♪<i> Settle down</i> ♪

26:31.907 --> 26:33.999
♪<i> Talk about</i>
<i> that one touchdown</i> ♪

26:34.135 --> 26:36.168
♪<i> Raise some kids</i> ♪

26:36.337 --> 26:38.912
♪<i> In red and black, go Bobcats</i> ♪

26:39.006 --> 26:41.323
♪<i> While the other half</i> ♪

26:41.342 --> 26:43.325
♪<i> Of our hometown</i> ♪

26:43.344 --> 26:45.436
♪<i> Was in the crowd</i> ♪

26:45.512 --> 26:48.606
♪<i> They knew the words,</i>
<i> they sang them loud</i> ♪

26:48.833 --> 26:51.683
♪<i> And all I want to do</i> ♪

26:51.836 --> 26:55.595
♪<i> Is make them proud</i> ♪

26:55.615 --> 26:58.532
♪<i> 'Cause half of me</i>
<i> will always be</i> ♪

27:00.344 --> 27:03.603
♪<i> From Knoxville, Tennessee</i> ♪

27:03.623 --> 27:06.206
♪<i> My hometown</i> ♪

27:07.793 --> 27:09.710
(vocalizing)

27:11.130 --> 27:12.946
♪<i> My hometown</i> ♪

27:12.965 --> 27:15.215
♪<i> My hometown.</i> ♪

27:17.786 --> 27:19.711
(laughs)

27:19.864 --> 27:21.764
(cheering, applause)

27:30.816 --> 27:32.816
Look at these cheekbones.

27:33.043 --> 27:35.377
Just like your mama's.

27:35.470 --> 27:37.971
I swear, that woman was born
with collagen in her veins.

27:38.065 --> 27:40.048
And a bourbon in her hand.

27:40.067 --> 27:41.975
Don't you look pretty.

27:42.069 --> 27:43.402
BOTH:
Thank you.

27:43.554 --> 27:44.828
-(laughs)
-(exhales): Well.

27:44.980 --> 27:46.221
I'll leave you two girls
to chat.

27:46.223 --> 27:47.572
Hmm.

27:47.725 --> 27:52.728
So, how would you feel about
filling in for me tonight?

27:52.746 --> 27:56.064
Tatum's so upset, and it all
just feels like such a lie.

27:56.083 --> 27:57.916
Well, that's because it is.

27:58.068 --> 28:00.493
But what-what other option
do you have?

28:00.513 --> 28:02.495
Open Horizon's
coming to see you.

28:02.515 --> 28:04.406
And say what you will
about Mama, but she didn't miss

28:04.425 --> 28:06.666
a show in 40 years,
whether she was hurting,

28:06.686 --> 28:08.744
grieving or in labor.

28:08.746 --> 28:10.412
That's what Luke said.

28:10.431 --> 28:12.931
And besides, this whole
industry is built on lies.

28:13.083 --> 28:15.267
You remember that photo shoot
I did for<i> Beaucoups</i> magazine?

28:15.419 --> 28:17.436
-Mm-hmm.
-They airbrushed me so hard

28:17.588 --> 28:19.604
my waist was about
as big around as your neck.

28:19.699 --> 28:22.032
-How dare they.
-I know.

28:22.184 --> 28:23.275
I was excited to do the shoot

28:23.427 --> 28:25.018
'cause I wanted to show
the world who I am,

28:25.112 --> 28:27.279
not buy into that
unattainable beauty crap

28:27.431 --> 28:29.522
they've been selling
my whole life.

28:29.691 --> 28:31.450
Well, screw<i> Beaucoups</i> magazine.

28:31.602 --> 28:34.461
Show the world who you are.
Show them your truth.

28:35.789 --> 28:37.464
Yeah.

28:45.257 --> 28:47.616
Hi, y'all. Um, I wanted
to clear something up.

28:47.709 --> 28:50.786
You may see some pictures of me
where I look like I weigh

28:50.804 --> 28:55.123
about a buck ten with no pores
and have a mane like a lion.

28:55.142 --> 28:58.235
But that girl, bless her
little airbrushed heart,

28:58.386 --> 29:00.796
she is not me or anybody real.

29:00.889 --> 29:02.722
So, thank God.

29:02.816 --> 29:04.557
This is me.

29:04.577 --> 29:07.411
I'm gonna show you
what my day is really like.

29:07.562 --> 29:09.988
(alarm beeping)

29:10.140 --> 29:12.657
So, this is what I look like
when I wake up.

29:12.752 --> 29:15.401
Uh, bed head, bad breath.

29:15.421 --> 29:16.661
Lovely.

29:16.814 --> 29:18.756
-(Summer crying)
-Then I change dirty diapers.

29:18.907 --> 29:20.999
Luckily, you can't smell that.

29:21.093 --> 29:22.667
Later on, I'll have some lunch.

29:22.820 --> 29:24.169
Not that you can tell
from those pictures,

29:24.321 --> 29:25.429
but the real Gigi actually eats.

29:25.580 --> 29:27.823
Usually, whatever
my daughter doesn't finish.

29:27.841 --> 29:31.510
So today it is
cold grilled cheese.

29:31.662 --> 29:33.178
Yummy.

29:33.272 --> 29:34.663
Mmm.

29:34.832 --> 29:37.257
Then I go to work, because
some people have to do that.

29:37.276 --> 29:39.184
After which I'll go home
and wash that pan

29:39.278 --> 29:40.778
I made the grilled cheese in.

29:40.929 --> 29:42.838
Because real people
do the dishes.

29:42.931 --> 29:45.115
So listen up, if you happen
to see that picture of me

29:45.267 --> 29:47.284
with the fake wind
blowing my fake hair

29:47.511 --> 29:49.027
as I bat my fake eyelashes,

29:49.179 --> 29:51.789
just know that's not me
or any other real woman.

29:51.940 --> 29:54.274
You don't need to look like
a Barbie doll to be beautiful,

29:54.368 --> 29:55.867
and anybody who says you do

29:55.961 --> 29:58.444
is the one with the problem,
not you.

29:58.464 --> 30:02.549
So screw you,
<i> Beaucoups</i> magazine.

30:07.473 --> 30:09.807
♪<i> I would say ooh, la, la</i> ♪

30:09.958 --> 30:11.350
♪<i> La, la, la, la, la.</i> ♪

30:17.799 --> 30:19.299
(cheering, applause)

30:19.318 --> 30:21.209
Hey, y'all, how you doing?

30:21.228 --> 30:23.562
Now, on behalf
of the Roman family

30:23.714 --> 30:25.063
and the entire Monarch team,

30:25.215 --> 30:26.639
I want to thank y'all
for coming out

30:26.733 --> 30:28.325
and helping us launch
Truthteller Bourbon.

30:28.552 --> 30:31.553
-(cheering)
-So I want all of you
to raise a glass,

30:31.722 --> 30:33.146
and get ready,

30:33.165 --> 30:36.241
'cause to help us celebrate
is my sister Nicky Roman,

30:36.335 --> 30:38.393
and right from the top
of the charts,

30:38.562 --> 30:39.503
Wade Stellings.

30:39.730 --> 30:41.630
(cheering, applause)

30:48.922 --> 30:52.074
-Nicky Roman.
-(both chuckle)

30:52.092 --> 30:54.834
-Are you ready?
-Let's go.

